Citation.sTitle: Vapor Liquid Equilibrium for the Trans-2-Butene + Methanol, + Ethanol, + 2-Propanol, + 2-Butanol and + 2-Methyl-2-Propanol Systems at 332 K
Citation.sAbstract: An automated static total pressure measurement apparatus was used to measure isothermal vapor-liquid equilibria for five binary systems: trans-2-butene + methanol, + ethanol, + 2-propanol, + 2-butanol and + 2-methyl-2-propanol at 332.3 K. Error analysis of the measured results has been presented. All systems exhibited positive deviation from Raoult's law. The trans-2-butene + methanol and trans-2-butene + ethanol systems showed azeotropic behavior.
